is that the money to educated the children in failing public schools was $15 thousand per child per year. Well, private schools would be given half that and enroll and educate the students.  These students and their families loved it as they finally got to go to a school that was not a hell hole but it was free to them. Since they were poor this was a huge blessing.  Obama killed the program but yet HIS DAUGHTERS GO TO ONE OF THE MOST EXPENSIVE PRIVATE SCHOOL IN THE NATION (It cost more than many colleges!!!).  What a hypocrite he is.  No, we do not need to have &quot;rich&quot; parents send their children to public schools.  We need to have vouchers and public charter schools so ALL PARENT'S have a choice, not just those blessed with adequate incomes to be able to pay for such. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1087" language="en" documentId="4275" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Mariner1776" date="Aug 29, 2013 5:30PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="7" thumbsDown="0" origId="4275" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1087"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>